\f1 \cf2 The purpose of this assignment is for you to develop an awareness of issues regarding the use and implementation of source code control systems.
\f0 \

\f1 You may work in teams of up to three people.
\f0 \

\f1 Design and develop a simple command-line source code control system. The system should be capable of satisfying the following requirements.
\f0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}Handle ASCII text files only.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Put a file under source code control.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Check in a modified version of a file after the user edits it.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Allow the user to associate a comment with each check-in.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Assign version numbers to all check-ins.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Check out the most current version of a file.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Check out any older version of a file by version number.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}List all versions of a file with their associated check-in comment.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Create a new source control branch for a file associating a unique user-chosen identifier with the new branch (the original branch should be called "main").
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}All of the above requirements should be satisfyable equally for all branches.
\f0 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1 {\listtext	\'95	}Generate a suggested file as the next version for branch X based on the last change applied to branch Y (where X and Y can be any non-equal branch names).
\f0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80

